body:
It's just one matmul in this demonstration, in reality more complex models are used.
You can only feed one input/state at a time, because the next state depends on the result.
I already asked this question on [StackOverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/48796619/why-is-tf-keras-inference-way-slower-than-numpy-operations).
